comments: Powell (LAC) reaches for the ball on his steal attempt and marginal follow-through contact occurs with Booker's (PHX) leg as he starts his drive toward the basket.
Hyland (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Hyland (LAC) contests the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Booker's (PHX) arm after the release.
Mann (LAC) initiates contact with Ayton's (PHX) back, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Mann (LAC) engages with Craig (PHX) and marginal contact occurs as he rests his hand on Craig's front during the rebound.
Craig's (PHX) hand slides off the ball and onto Westbrook's (LAC) arm, which affects his SQBR as he returns to the ground after securing the rebound.
Gordon (LAC) and Durant (PHX) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Hyland (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball on his steal attempt after Craig (PHX) receives the pass on the perimeter.
Hyland (LAC) grasps and releases Craig's (PHX) jersey as marginal contact occurs before Craig makes his intended pass.

Booker (PHX) moves alongside Westbrook's (LAC) path and makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it during the driving shot attempt. Any follow-through arm contact after the ball is dislodged is deemed incidental.
Booker (PHX) is established in Westbrook's (LAC) path and absorbs the marginal contact as Westbrook lunges toward the basket during the post-shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) and Booker (PHX) both make clean contact with the ball as they pursue the rebound.

Powell (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball to temporarily dislodge it from Durant (PHX) on the perimeter and any follow-through contact with Durant's arm after the dislodge is deemed incidental. Durant legally steps on the midcourt line while recovering the loose ball.
Hyland (LAC) briefly grasps and immediately releases Paul's (PHX) jersey shorts as marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Westbrook (LAC) legally contests Booker's (PHX) jump shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) briefly grasps Hyland's (LAC) off-arm and marginal contact occurs as they both reach for the loose ball and Ayton cleanly taps away the rebound.
Powell (LAC) initiates contact with Booker's (PHX) body, which alters his driving shot attempt.
Craig (PHX) makes contact with Powell's (LAC) arm during his upward shooting motion, which affects his jump shot attempt. A shooting foul is correctly assessed.
Hyland (LAC) makes clean contact with the ball on his steal attempt as Durant (PHX) receives the pass.
Powell (LAC) commits a take foul on Paul (PHX).
Okogie (PHX) legally contests Hyland's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Mann (LAC) is unable to secure the rebound and Durant (PHX) avoids contact with Mann's arm during his pursuit of the loose ball.
Mann (LAC) commits a take foul on Durant (PHX).
Craig (PHX) adjusts to Powell's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the start of the drive.

Hyland (LAC) grabs and pulls Booker's (PHX) jersey away from his body, affecting Booker's (PHX) FOM during the inbound. The illegal contact occurs prior to the inbound pass being released and an away from the play foul should be assessed.
Westbrook (LAC) moves into and extends his forearm to initiate contact with Durant's (PHX) body, which affects Durant's SQBR during the drive.
